When viewing a commit that contains a change to a submodule, FishEye shows that the submodule was changed, but it does not display a diff.

For example, suppose I have a submodule at {{modules/log}} pointing to commit {{123456}}.  I then change it to point to commit {{abcdef}} and commit that change.  FishEye shows:

{code}
modules/log (+1 -1)
No Change
{code}

Instead of this, which is what Git would show:

{code}
modules/log (+1 -1)
-Subproject commit 123456
+Subproject commit abcdef
{code}

the line "foo/bar name" in raw-mime.types maps the foo/bar mime type to files named *.name and files named <any single character>name, e.g. 1name, 2name, xname etc.

See CustomFileNameMap where idx is set to zero when it should be left at -1.

{code}
public String getContentTypeFor(String fileName) {
        int idx = fileName.lastIndexOf('.');
        if (idx == -1) {
            idx = 0;
        }
        if (fileName.length() == idx) {
            return null;
        }
        String ext = fileName.substring(idx + 1); //BUG: when idx is zero we strip one character from the name
        return mMapping.get(ext);
    }
{code}

In the Database Configuration settings (Admin > Databases), the test connection button shows an invalid message when the database is not using a Unicode encoding.

It says:
{noformat}
The database is case insensitive. Crucible requires that the database use a case sensitive collation
{noformat}
whereas, to reflect the actual check, it should be:
{noformat}
The database is not using Unicode. Crucible requires that the database uses a UTF8 encoding to support internalization.
{noformat}

