Perforce allows you to have a mapping in a branchspec where the source and target directory are the same.
E.g.
{noformat}
//depot1/...  //depot1/...
//depot2/doo  //depot2/dah
{noformat}
The first line makes no sense, but is easy to create by accident especially as Perforce populates a new branchspec by default with such mappings.
FishEye will interpret this branchspec and show files in {{//depot1/...}} as if they belong to a branch, which is confusing.
If FishEye can ignore such branchspec mappings it avoids confusion and maybe also has a performance benefit.

